} In Tanzania, history is replete with sad cases of such leaders The two countries have a long history of taking retaliatory actions against each other. Nine candidates are fighting to replace Boniface Kabaka who died last year. Ex-Epra boss Pavel Oimeke resigned last week from to venture into politics. Andayi says it was unfortunate that the NLC official died under mysterious circumstances.